A Makadara court has sentenced a woman who faked her abduction to eight months imprisonment. Makadara Principal Magistrate Hellen Onkwany sentenced Mary Ambeza last Friday after she pleaded guilty to the offence. The court heard that Ambeza had on February 7, given false information to Dominic Oduor Otieno who is her husband that she had been abducted by unknown people. This forced Otieno to report the matter to Dandora police station in Kamkunji Sub County in Nairobi. Ambeza is said to have informed  Oduor that she had been abducted in a message that also read "come and collect your wife body". “The information led officer Judy Mwau to book the report in the occurrence book vide OB 42/06/02/2022 at 2228hrs, the information you knew to be false...," read the charge sheet in part. According to the facts read in court, Otieno said his wife Ambeza went to her workplace and failed to return prompting him to call her but her phone was off. “Later, around 21 hours, he got a message through his wife’s phone number reading, "come and collect your wife body"," the report read in part. The victim has a gang rape case that is pending before the court. Two suspects linked to gang-rape case are being held at Industrial area GK prison.